<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-03 00:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arson Fire Kills Four Children  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- An intruder splashed a flammable liquid on the floor of
an apartment and sparked a blaze Wednesday night that killed four children,
authorities said.
</P>
<P>
	   The person had knocked on the door of the house and asked by name for the
mother of the children, who was not home. He then set the apartment on fire and
fled, Jefferson Parish authorities said.
</P>
<P>
	   An elderly man in the home, identified as the grandfather, was able to rush
two children to safety, but four others ran up to the second floor of the
apartment because they were frightened by the flames, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
	   The man was turned back by intense smoke and heat when he tried to return
for them.
</P>
<P>
	   Firefighters made their way inside as they fought the blaze and found the
bodies of the remaining children.
</P>
<P>
	   Authorities did not immediately release the names of the victims, their
mother or the family members who escaped.
</P>
<P>
	   Family and neighbors could be seen sobbing outside the smoldering apartment,
which was part of a complex in an area known as Harvey, across the Mississippi
River from New Orleans. Jefferson Parish authorities referred to it as a
high-crime area.
</P>
<P>
	   Red Cross officials said four families were forced out of neighboring
apartments.
</P>
<P>
	   Authorities had a vague description of the intruder but no name and few
other leads, said Sheriff Harry Lee.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
