<HEADLINE> Warriors 101, Grizzlies 95  </HEADLINE>
    By DENNIS GEORGATOS AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
	   OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) -- Mookie Blaylock scored 25 points, including nine in
the fourth quarter, as the Golden State Warriors rallied to beat the Vancouver
Grizzlies 101-95 Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
	   Antawn Jamison added 21 points and John Starks, playing for the second time
since missing 10 games with a knee injury, added 17 for the Warriors, who
matched a season-high by winning their third straight. Golden State has won five
of seven since snapping a 12-game losing streak.
</P>
<P>
	   Shareef Abdur-Rahim had 25 points to lead Vancouver. Michael Dickerson added
19 points, Mike Bibby had 13 and Bryant Reeves 10, all in the second half.
</P>
<P>
	   Blaylock also matched a season-high with 10 assists, including a feed that
led to a layup by Jamison with 32 seconds remaining for a 96-93 Warriors' lead.
</P>
<P>
	   Golden State was ahead most of the game but began the fourth quarter with a
four-point deficit.
</P>
<P>
	   Three straight 3-pointers by Donyell Marshall, Starks and Blaylock offset a
3-pointer by Dennis Scott and a layup by Reeves as Golden State moved into an
85-all tie with 6:02 remaining.
</P>
<P>
	   Vancouver moved back in front when Scott hit another 3-pointer but Blaylock
answered by draining his fourth 3-pointer of the night to put the Warriors up
92-91 with 1:58 left.
</P>
<P>
	   Golden State didn't trail again, though Abdur-Rahim's layup with 27 seconds
narrowed the gap to a point. But Starks, Blaylock and Marshall combined to make
five of six free throws down the stretch to secure the win.
</P>
<P>
	   Trailing by six at the half, the Grizzlies used a third-quarter surge to
take their first lead of the game. Abdur-Rahim fueled the rally, scoring 12 of
his points in the period.
</P>
<P>
	   After Jason Caffey's putback put Golden State up 67-64 with 3:31 left in the
third, Dickerson dunked off an alley-oop from Abdur-Rahim despite being fouled.
</P>
<P>
	   Dickerson made the free throw to complete the three-point play and start a
10-0 run that carried the Grizzlies to a 74-67 lead. Abdur-Rahim had a pair of
free throws and a driving layup before Dickerson capped the flurry with another
three-point play as Vancouver led 76-72 after three quarters.
</P>
<P>
	   Jamison scored 15 of his points in the first half, helping Golden State take
51-45 lead.
</P>
<P>
	   Bibby converted a three-point play that pulled the Grizzlies within three
but Blaylock came back to hit a 3-pointer in the final seconds of the second
quarter.
</P>
</TEXT>
