<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 68; Nasdaq Climbs 67  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up 68 points in today's
early going. Advancing issues on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 2-1 lead
over decliners.
</P>
<P>
	   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 67 points and the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
Stock Index is up eleven points.
</P>
<P>
	   Stock prices are riding on the back of a very bullish move in the bond
market today.
</P>
<P>
	   The price of the benchmark bond is soaring after the government yesterday
said it would reduce the number of bonds it auctions.
</P>
<P>
	   And with lower interest rates in the bond market, it's allowing stock
investors to look past yesterday's much-anticipated rate hike by the Federal
Reserve.
</P>
<P>
	   Also, there is reason for optimism in the high-tech arena. Even though
Amazon.com reported a wider loss than had been expected, it forecast a narrowing
of its losses as the year moves forward.
</P>
</TEXT>
