<HEADLINE> Money Market Funds Up $3.6B  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- Assets of the nation's retail money market mutual funds
rose by $3.60 billion in the latest week to $964.02 billion, the Investment
Company Institute said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
	   Assets of taxable money market funds in the retail category rose by $2.63
billion to $799.82 billion for the week ended Wednesday, the Washington-based
mutual fund trade group said. Tax-exempt fund assets rose by $971.1 million to
$164.20 billion.
</P>
<P>
	   Assets of institutional money market funds fell by $16.52 billion to $695.89
billion for the same period. Among institutional funds, taxable money market
fund assets fell by $17.44 billion to $644.18 billion; assets of tax-exempt
funds rose by $912.7 million to $51.71 billion.
</P>
<P>
	   Total money market assets stood at $1.660 trillion for the week.
</P>
<P>
	   Assets for the previous week were revised to $1.673 trillion to reflect
reporting errors and a change in the number of funds reporting.
</P>
<P>
	   The seven-day average yield on money market mutual funds rose in the week
ended Tuesday to 5.14 percent from 5.11 percent the previous week, said IBC's
Money Fund Report, a trade journal published in Ashland, Mass., by IBC Financial
Data Inc. The 30-day average yield rose to 5.13 percent from 5.07 percent, IBC
Financial Data said.
</P>
<P>
	   The seven-day compounded yield rose to 5.28 percent from 5.24 percent the
previous week, and the 30-day compounded yield rose to 5.26 percent from 5.20
percent, IBC Financial Data said.
</P>
<P>
	   The average maturity of the portfolios held by money funds was 45 days, up
from 44 days, IBC Financial Data said.
</P>
<P>
	   The online service bankrate.com said its survey of 100 leading commercial
banks, savings and loan associations and savings banks in the nation's 10
largest markets showed the annual percentage yield available on money market
accounts remained unchanged at 2.07 percent as of Wednesday from a week earlier.
</P>
<P>
	   The North Palm Beach, Fla.-based unit of Intelligent Life Corp. said the
annual percentage yield available on interest-bearing checking accounts held
steady at 0.84 percent.
</P>
<P>
	   Bankrate.com said the annual percentage yield was 4.72 percent on six-month
certificates of deposit, up from 4.71 percent the previous week. Yields were
5.08 percent on 1-year CDs, up from 5.05 percent; 5.32 percent on 2 1/2-year
CDs, up from 5.30 percent; and 5.63 percent on 5-year CDs, up from 5.60 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
