<HEADLINE> Ladies' Robes Recalled  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- A New York City company is recalling about 2,100 ladies'
robes because they can catch fire too easily.
</P>
<P>
	   HANRO USA Inc. has received one report that a robe ignited when exposed to
flame and burned a woman's hair, the Consumer Product Safety Commission said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
	   The five different styles of recalled robes, which are made with 90 percent
cotton and 10 percent polyester fleece fabric, contain the sewn-in label ``HANRO
of Switzerland.'' They were sold in white, blue, ivory, beige and gray, and in
sizes XS through L.
</P>
<P>
	   Department stores and boutiques nationwide sold the robes from October 1998
through January 2000 for between $280 to $350.
</P>
<P>
	   The safety commission advises consumers to immediately stop using the robes
and return them to the store where purchased for a refund and a $50 HANRO gift
certificate.
</P>
<P>
	   For more information, consumers can contact HANRO USA at 1-800-889-7443
between 9 a.m. and 5 p.m. EST Monday through Friday.
</P>
