<HEADLINE> Fla. Gunman Kills Officer  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- A man pulled over on a traffic stop opened fire on two
police officers Thursday, killing one with a shot to the head and seriously
injuring the other, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
	   The officers were trying to arrest the alleged shooter, Emmanuel St. Nattis,
of Miami, on outstanding robbery charges.
</P>
<P>
	   Officer George S. DeSalvia, 29, was pronounced brain dead and Officer Edward
A. Diaz, 28, was in serious condition at the Orlando Regional Medical Center
with wounds to his back and shoulder.
</P>
<P>
	   It was the first shooting death of an Orlando Police officer since 1976.
</P>
<P>
	   ``Early this morning in Orlando, a piece of all of us died,'' said Mayor
Glenda Hood.
</P>
<P>
	   Police charged 22-year-old St. Nattis with first-degree murder of a police
officer, assault and battery of a police officer and attempted carjacking.
</P>
<P>
	   He was found in an abandoned house near the shooting scene after a six-hour
search by more than 150 law officers.
</P>
