<BODY>
<HEADLINE> School bus driver cited for crash that injured 24  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
    	   GERRY, N.Y. (AP) - A school bus driver was ticketed in a five-vehicle
collision Thursday that injured 14 people, including a 10 students traveling to
an afternoon swim meet.
<P>
	   None of the injuries, which ranged from back and neck to foot and hand
complaints, required hospitalization.
</P>
<P>
	   The Chautauqua County Sheriff's Department accused bus driver Shirley
Engels, 56, for following too closely.
</P>
<P>
	   Deputies said she hit two vehicles that were waiting to make a left turn.
The first vehicle crossed the center lane and hit an oncoming car. The bus also
entered opposing lanes and hit another vehicle head-on, according to deputies.
The wreck shut down traffic for about two hours.
</P>
<P>
	   The bus carried the Franklinville High School swim team, a chaperone and a
coach. The students range in age from 12 to 18.
</P>
</TEXT>
