<HEADLINE> Bucks 102, Jazz 99  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    SALT LAKE CITY(AP) -- Glenn Robinson's 3-pointer at the buzzer gave the
Milwaukee Bucks a 102-99 victory over Utah Thursday night, giving the Jazz a
five-game losing streak for the first time in almost six years.
</P>
<P>
	   With the score tied 99-99, Robinson took an inbounds pass from Vinny Del
Negro and stepped back and sank the shot over the outstretched arm of Adam
Keefe. Robinson was 4-for-4 on 3-pointers.
</P>
<P>
	   Ray Allen, who scored a season-high 36 points for Milwaukee, made 5-of-7
3-pointers. Allen and hit three free throws in the final minute to help the
Bucks win for the first time in eight games at the Delta Center.
</P>
<P>
	   Karl Malone led the Jazz with 28 points. John Stockton added 18, Bryon
Russell 14 and Jeff Hornacek 12.
</P>
<P>
	   There were 23 lead changes and 18 ties. Every time the Jazz charged, Allen
answered. Allen sank 3-of-4 free throws in the final minute to give the Bucks a
99-97 advantage.
</P>
<P>
	   Stockton answered with a driving layup with 2.6 seconds remaining to tie it
99-99.
</P>
<P>
	   Robinson, selected to join Allen as an East All-Star reserve, hit a long
jumper with 1:00 remaining to give the Bucks a 96-95 lead. Karl Malone answered
with two free throws to reclaim the advantage for Utah.
</P>
<P>
	   The Jazz haven't lost five consecutive games since March 1994, a stretch of
435 games.
</P>
<P>
	   Malone put Utah ahead 79-77 with 9:57 remaining with an 18-foot jumper from
the right side. The Bucks are accustomed to Malone's big games, having seen him
score a season-high 40 points on Nov. 20 at Milwaukee.
</P>
<P>
	   Notes: After the opening minute of play, Hornacek reached the 30,000-minute
mark for his career. ... Malone gave Bucks coach George Karl a playful smack to
the head after inbounding the ball in front of the visitors' bench in the first
quarter. ... Play was stopped three times during the game due to mechanical
problems with the game clock.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
